<item>
            <title>[LU-520] Test scripts contain spurious test start markers that indicate the start of false tests.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-520</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Test scripts create a spurious test start marker at the start of the test suite. Any example can be seen below in that the marker contains an indicator of a test called &apos;conf-sanity_sh_tes&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lustre-mixed-el5-x86_64 #1301: Tests running for 203 minutes, 0 restarts, current suite:test conf-sanity:test_59&lt;br/&gt;
1 sessions running&lt;br/&gt;
lustre-mixed-el5-x86_64 #1301: Tests running for 204 minutes, 0 restarts, current suite:test recovery-small:conf-sanity_sh_tes&lt;br/&gt;
1 sessions running&lt;br/&gt;
lustre-mixed-el5-x86_64 #1301: Tests running for 205 minutes, 0 restarts, current suite:test recovery-small:test_1&lt;br/&gt;
1 sessions running&lt;/p&gt;</description>
